%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EThe%20women%20trained%20in%20the%20stitching%20school%20have%20now%20found%20new%20means%20of%20income%20and%20are%20sustaining%20their%20families.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20participatory%20model%2C%20she%20explained%2C%20ensures%20transparency%20and%20connection.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20donors%20know%20exactly%20where%20the%20money%20goes%20%E2%80%94%20into%20machines%2C%20materials%2C%20trainers%E2%80%99%20salaries%2C%20and%20sometimes%20even%20tea%20for%20the%20learners.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EStitching%20futures%2C%20one%20garment%20at%20a%20time%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20just%20over%20two%20years%2C%20SAHAS%20has%20trained%20more%20than%20100%20women.%20Some%20now%20work%20independently%20from%20home%2C%20others%20continue%20to%20fulfil%20orders%20through%20the%20NGO.%20A%20few%20have%20even%20started%20training%20newcomers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKaushalya%20said%20she%E2%80%99s%20now%20confident%20in%20taking%20on%20work%20from%20neighbours.%20%E2%80%9CI%20stitched%20a%20%3Cem%3Ekurta%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20someone%20in%20the%20colony%20last%20week.%20They%20paid%20me%20and%20said%20they%E2%80%99ll%20recommend%20me%20to%20others.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMannu%20hopes%20to%20learn%20embroidery%20next.%20%E2%80%9CI%20want%20to%20stitch%20suits%20for%20women%20in%20my%20colony%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said.%20%E2%80%9CAnd%20maybe%20one%20day%2C%20I%E2%80%99ll%20have%20my%20own%20little%20shop.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeeta%2C%20who%20is%20still%20learning%20to%20read%2C%20wants%20to%20sew%20her%20granddaughter%E2%80%99s%20school%20uniform%20next%20year.%20%E2%80%9CWith%20my%20own%20hands%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20her%20voice%20swelling%20with%20quiet%20determination.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20broken.%20We%20were%20just%20waiting%20to%20begin.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20its%20heart%2C%20this%20story%20isn%E2%80%99t%20about%20a%20sewing%20machine%20or%20a%20skill.%20It%E2%80%99s%20about%20the%20first%20time%20a%20woman%20held%20a%20pencil.%20The%20first%20time%20she%20realised%20she%20could%20make%20something%20and%20sell%20it.%20The%20first%20time%20she%20earned%2C%20and%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20ask.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Chopra%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CChange%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20have%20to%20start%20with%20something%20big.%20It%20begins%20with%20one%20step.%20One%20skill.%20One%20woman%20finding%20her%20voice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20encourages%20anyone%20who%20wants%20to%20contribute%2C%20whether%20with%20fabric%2C%20time%2C%20or%20funds%2C%20to%20reach%20out.%20%E2%80%9CIf%20you%20have%20a%20skill%2C%20teach%20it.%20If%20you%20can%20donate%20something%2C%20do%20it.%20It%20all%20goes%20into%20building%20someone%E2%80%99s%20confidence.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20world%20that%20often%20tells%20women%20to%20stay%20small%2C%20this%20tailoring%20room%20tells%20a%20different%20story.%20The%20machines%20may%20be%20old.%20The%20walls%20may%20be%20bare.%20But%20the%20futures%20being%20stitched%20together%20here%20are%20full%20of%20colour%2C%20courage%2C%20and%20possibility.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEach%20garment%20made%20is%20more%20than%20fabric.%20It%20is%20proof%20that%20every%20woman%20who%20picks%20up%20a%20needle%20here%20is%20not%20just%20making%20clothes.%20She%E2%80%99s%20making%20her%20place%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1752028200000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F07%2FTBI-FEATURED-IMAGE-2025-07-08T172815.759-1751976045.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D463107%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22This%20isn%E2%80%99t%20just%20a%20stitching%20class.%20It%E2%80%99s%20where%20200%2B%20women%20are%20reclaiming%20self-worth%20through%20employment%2C%20skills%2C%20and%20basic%20education%20in%20a%20place%20built%20on%20sisterhood%20and%20compassion.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%